he best pvpers in this game once we hit 50+<br>As long as you have decent resists ( around 100 ), know how to jouste, and know how to use pvp skillz in general.<br>If the class can't cast (warriors, rogues, monks) I win automatically unless they have run3 (cause i don't =P)<br><br>Clerics aren't even a challenge......seriously =P<br><br>Enchanters are ez if you have counteract poison memmed and you have good resists. (I only have 94MR and can resist almost all magic based spells from a chanter)<br><br>Wizzies, mages, and Necros tend to be a bit harder.  If you are in an open zone they will own you almost all of the time.  If you are in a dungeon however they will not win, if they begin to cast a spell you go behind a wall and they can't cast cause they need a clear casting area. After they cast you come out slash em once with your 2her, they begin to cast again, go hide behind the wall till they're finished casting.  If necro sends pet, be ready with spook the dead.  Mage pets i usually root then take out the mage.  Wizzy pets i usually take out first cause they're the base mana/resists/see invis of the wizard.<br><br>If fighting a paladin like mentioned above both paladins will get very bored and it will take awhile =P<br><br>If i'm fighting a higher level shadowknight and his HT is up i'll loose sometimes.  Yes we have LoH but if he uses HT when we have 1.5bubs it will usually kill us. ( i don't use LoH in a pvp battle until i'm below 1 bub usually.)<br><br>If your resists are low some good gear to get are:<br>2 BD Bracers<br>2 velium diamond rings<br>2 BD earings<br>BD choker<br>...basically all the bd gear you can get =)<br>If stats are badly needed you could get the Bracer of Might and Bracer of Fortitude in UP, adds 6 saves to all and +15str or sta (depending on bracer) and 12ac.<br><br>Thats my input on how we fair in pvp =)<br><br>Sumdyar Pureblood<br>Cavalier of Tunare<br>51st season! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><t