6 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agree with Ennder</span><hr size=1> Bards, Pallies, Sks, Necros, and Mage after the new pet changes on test come live.<br><br>However, if a rogue gets the jump on you, you only have a few seconds to react. <p>"History is just a set of lies agreed upon" - Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unoracsilverblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norac Silverblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/26/02 12:44:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agree with Ennder</span><hr size=1> Just my 2 coppers here.<br><br>I'm a lvl 53 pally, with pretty decent gear (mostly DW and Valorium combo).  I also wield a polished shai din naginata although I'd rather have a lance of narandis hehe or something even more frightening <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I ALWAYS duel with high resist gear because a single mezz or a well landed DoT when u are low on mana can have your butt handed back to you on a silver plateau...<br><br>My best duel ever was at lvl 51 against a lvl 54 epic rogue. Of course my spells werent landing on him, but I still managed to land a FOL on him once, where I beat on his back for a lot of damage, seemed I was doing the backstabbing now hehe.  Although I dont play on a PvP, I never miss a chance to duel, being a former highly ranked UT player, cause I kinda like the head-to-head aspect of dueling <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Anyhow, the first thing that makes someone better than another in duels is knowing that even blinded, tashed, rooted, DoTed you STILL have things to do better than panic.  And one thing that is simply crucial, is learning to joust by toggling the attack on / attack off button.  This has made me win more duels than I could dream of simply by straffing, running like a headless chicken and when ready to strike, I would turn around and BAM BAM double knocker for 150 140...  No rogue can withstand this type of DMG...<br><br>Trick is to go with a good 2HS to inflict as much DMG per available attack (a key element of jousting) as possible. I know using a 1HS + shield seems to &quot;land&quot; more damage on the opponent, but my friend and I (both same lvl pallies) have been going head to head so often that we both agree about the 2HS jousting technique.<br><br>My worst duel ever...I lost to a red-conning ranger. Well, he wouldnt lemme see his lvl the bastard, but I figured I'd own him anyways with his green pantyhoses...even with his swiftwind... Since I already owned pretty much all other melees except SKs which I would only duel if of same lvl, I had no real reason to fear....  Can you imagine my surprise when he started running like a freak as soon as I accepted his duel invitation and started landing nuclear bombs on me with his freaking bow?  He was hitting me just as hard as a lvl 75 golem for crying out loud....this was my first encounter with a ranger stuffed with AA points in trueshot ability hahaha...not a funny thing to do!<br><br>After many many months of dueling, here is my ownn appreciation of other classes versus ours (bear in mind that I am only nearing 54 now, so changes could happen past this lvl)....<br><br>Opponent  /  Advantage  / Tip<br>Mage  /  Mage  /  Cancel magic on pet + FOL/root, go for mage<br>Necro  /  Even  /  FOL or spook, bye bye pet, go for necro with DD stuns and Flame (kill before DoTs do their trick, helm heal until DoTs wear off after);<br>Wizard  /  Pally / Easy like hell, get CR up and FR up, be wary of manaburn though;<br>Bard  /  Bard / I know bards that NEVER lose duels if they are patient;<br>Enchanter / Paladin / Cure poison = bye bye tash, high MR, kill chanter, dont bother on pet, chanter pet = green orc pawn;<br>Ranger / Paladin / If snared dont chase, self heal with helm if he starts shelling bombs at you with his freaking bow... head-to-head they fold like a lawnchair under Pally pummeling;<br>SKs / Even / It comes to gear, tactics and JOUSTING. Dont FOL, Stun or root, keep mana for heals. Dont accept a fight with his pet already up...<br>Monks / Pally / they can be tough if u are unprepared... Monks often have lower resists (cant carry as much gear as we do) so dont accept for him to say &quot;heading to bank and coming back&quot; (he is gonna get his resist gear)<br>Warriors / Pally / Unless the guy is a couple levels above, it's a fairly easy fight, LOH at 1/4 of your own bar, he should have no more than 1/3...if he can go thru you twice, he deserves to win... dont bother casting, you lose DMG per round<br>BST / never dueled a BST, so go figure!<br>Pally / Pally = pain in the arse and very long fight.<br>Shaman / Pally / they will try to debuff you and slow you to a crawl...make sure u have sow potions to follow them wherever they try to go hide and med...<br>Druids / Druid / These guys can really mess you up in zones like WK or BW.  Lots of trees and stuff where they can hide and med after they used SOC to outrun you even with SOW potions.  BE PATIENT....I never met a druid within a couple levels that could nuke me to death. Just med and heal if he flees, he will eventually be in your reach (CANCEL magic hoping to dispell his sow).<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usuperhornyfrog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Super Horny Frog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 3:05:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agree with Ennder</span><hr size=1> If ya wanna make a rogue (or any duel wielding mellee) have a really bad day, get a Shammy DS potion or 8th coldain ring. (smart PvP/Duelers should have cancel magic potions though)<br><br>And as for neutralizing rangers bows, use hills and stand next to a wall.  Seem to remember that for some reason when standing right next to a wall arrows won't hit ya for some reason.<br><br>Toadhammer Blazingberad<br>Crusader of Brell<br>Fennin Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugathorneci.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GathornEci</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/14/02 11:05:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladins = Best PvP Class?</span><hr size=1> I don't believe you can be hit with arrows while on a horse. <p><p><html><center><p>Sir Gathorn<br>Crusader of E'ci<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=142065">My Profile</a></center></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BOR